column41: When we opened LARDO in 2012, our goal wasn’t complicated: authentic food, cooked simply, and eaten well. One of the key principles we wanted to convey was a sense of place, where we integrated ourselves into the fabric of the local neighbourhood. We wanted our customers to feel a sense of ownership, a belonging, that LARDO was theirs, a second home. We wanted it to feel as if it had been there forever, we wanted it to have life – energy and heart.
